               <placeName>Mäkaʿǝlo Mäkanä Lǝʿul</placeName>
               <placeName type="alt">Mäkaʿǝlo</placeName>
               <country>Ethiopia</country>
               <region>Tǝgray</region>
               <settlement from="2011-11-16" to="2011-11-16">wäräda Gulo Mäkäda, ṭabiya Ḥabän, qušät Mäkaʿǝlo</settlement>
               <location>
                  <geo>14.411504 39.465905</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2230.0</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1500" notAfter="1600">1500-1600</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Founded possibly during the time of King Särṣä Dǝngǝl (r. 1563–97).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gädam. It is still considered a monastery, but there are no monks. A small recent church dedicated to Yǝmaʾta is located on the other side of the road, on the rock, close to ʿAddi Qolqwal (AQG). The church of Däbrä Maʿṣo Yoḥannǝs and it's flat-top mountain can be seen from the compound of Mäkaʿǝlo. &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">12 Mss photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg001">MKMG-001</ref> “ Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg002">MKMG-002</ref> “ Prayer of Incense”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg003">MKMG-003</ref> “ Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg004">MKMG-004</ref> “ Synaxarion (September-February)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg005">MKMG-005</ref> “Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg006">MKMG-006</ref> “ Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg007">MKMG-007</ref> “Vita of  Zä-Mikaʾel Arägawi”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg008">MKMG-008</ref> “ The Book of Baptism”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg009">MKMG-009</ref> “ Synaxarion (March-February)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg010">MKMG-010</ref> “ The Rite of the Holy Week”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg011">MKMG-011</ref> “The Book of Gǝṣṣǝw”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmkmg012">MKMG-012</ref> “Miracles of Mary”.</ab>
